11#ifndef COMMON_VIDEO_H264_SPS_PARSER_H_
12#define COMMON_VIDEO_H264_SPS_PARSER_H_
13
14#include "absl/types/optional.h"
15
16#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
17#include <cstdint>
18#endif
19
20namespace rtc {
21class BitBuffer;
22}
23
24namespace webrtc {
25
26// A class for parsing out sequence parameter set (SPS) data from an H264 NALU.
27class SpsParser {
28 public:
29 // The parsed state of the SPS. Only some select values are stored.
30 // Add more as they are actually needed.
31 struct SpsState {
32 SpsState();
33 SpsState(const SpsState&);
34 ~SpsState();
35
36 uint32_t width = 0;
37 uint32_t height = 0;
38 uint32_t delta_pic_order_always_zero_flag = 0;
39 uint32_t separate_colour_plane_flag = 0;
40 uint32_t frame_mbs_only_flag = 0;
41 uint32_t log2_max_frame_num = 4; // Smallest valid value.
42 uint32_t log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb = 4; // Smallest valid value.
43 uint32_t pic_order_cnt_type = 0;
44 uint32_t max_num_ref_frames = 0;
45 uint32_t vui_params_present = 0;
46 uint32_t id = 0;
47 };
48
49 // Unpack RBSP and parse SPS state from the supplied buffer.
50 static absl::optional<SpsState> ParseSps(const uint8_t* data, size_t length);
51
52 protected:
53 // Parse the SPS state, up till the VUI part, for a bit buffer where RBSP
54 // decoding has already been performed.
55 static absl::optional<SpsState> ParseSpsUpToVui(rtc::BitBuffer* buffer);
56};
57
58} // namespace webrtc
59#endif // COMMON_VIDEO_H264_SPS_PARSER_H_
